<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/narn/plot/NarrativeElement> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/narn/plot/NarrativeUnit> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The narrative unit in which this element appears."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "occurs in unit"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "located in unit"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/occursInUnit> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "The Falling Action occurs in Part III."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/narn/plot/Story> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/narn/plot/PlotDevice> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a story to the plot devices it employs."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "uses device"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "employs device"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/plot/usesDevice> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "The Narn uses devices: Dramatic Irony, Anagnorisis, Peripeteia."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Describes a spatial relation where two regions are strictly disjoint and share no spatial points."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "disconnected"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "disjoint regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Angband and Doriath are disconnected since they share no spatial regions."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/borders> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Denotes a relation where the boundaries of two regions intersect while their interiors remain disjoint."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "externally connected"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "touching regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Brethil is externally connected to Doriath because their boundaries touch."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/contains> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/isAPartOf> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ReflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents spatial equivalence where two distinct entities occupy the exact identical spatial extent."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "equal"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "coextensive regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EQ> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "The Thousand Caves and Menegroth are spatially equal entities."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/isAPartOf> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Specifies a relation where the primary region is strictly contained within the interior of the secondary region with no shared boundary points."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "non-tangential proper part"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "interior part"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Dor-lómin is a non-tangential proper part of Hithlum as it is completely enclosed."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/contains> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#TransitiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The inverse relation where the primary region completely and strictly contains the secondary region within its interior."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "non-tangential proper part inverse"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "interior whole"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Hithlum is the non-tangential proper part inverse of Dor-lómin."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates that two regions share a common interior subset without either fully subsuming the other."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "partially overlapping"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "overlapping regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/PO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "The wild lands partially overlap with Brethil."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/isAPartOf> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Defines a state where the primary region is entirely subsumed by the secondary region while sharing at least one boundary point."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "tangential proper part"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "tangential part"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Hithlum is a tangential proper part of Beleriand."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/contains> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPP> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The inverse relation where the primary region completely subsumes the secondary region while sharing boundary points."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "tangential proper part inverse"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "tangential whole"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/TPPi> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Beleriand represents the tangential proper part inverse of Hithlum."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/Place> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/Place> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The most general spatial relation between two regions."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "spatially related to"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "spatial relation"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Doriath is spatially related to Brethil."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Denotes the tragic act of a character intentionally taking their own life."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "committed suicide"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "took own life"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/committedSuicide> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Túrin fell into despair and committed suicide with his sword Gurthang."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Describes an act where a character invokes supernatural malevolence or a curse upon another."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "cursed"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "placed a curse on"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/cursed> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Mîm sought revenge and cursed Andróg after the killing of Khîm."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Denotes a state of dread or apprehension regarding another character."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "feared"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "had fear of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/feared> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Glaurung recognized the threat and feared Túrin."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Defines a broad emotional directedness or sentiment from one character toward another."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has emotional relation with"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "feels towards"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Saeros holds a deep emotional relation rooted in hatred towards Túrin."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a symmetric and mutual bond of friendship between two entities."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has friend"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "is a friend of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasFriend> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Túrin maintains a mutual friendship and has friend Sador."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#FunctionalProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/EmotionalValence> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Functionally assigns a specific emotional state or valence to a relational entity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "has valence"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "has sentiment"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasValence> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Húrin acts functionally and has valence positive."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/hasEmotionalRelationWith> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a profound sentiment of malice or hatred directed at another entity."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hated"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "had hatred for"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hated> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Saeros harbored intense resentment and hated Túrin."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates the act of subjecting another character to a mental spell or hypnotic enchantment."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "hypnotised"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "cast a spell on"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/hypnotised> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Glaurung used his power and hypnotised Níniel."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Represents a symmetric bond based on shared familial lineage or blood relation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is a kinsman of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "kin of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAKinsmanOf> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Túrin shares a bloodline and is a kinsman of Nienor."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/wasServedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Defines a fundamentally antagonistic and hostile relationship."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is an enemy of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "foe of"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isAnEnemyOf> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Morgoth stands as a prime antagonist and is an enemy of Húrin."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Denotes a formal and symmetric matrimonial relationship between two entities."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "is married to"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "wed to"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/isMarriedTo> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Turambar formalized his bond and is married to Níniel."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#AsymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/narn/social/served> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/social/killed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Indicates a fatal action where the subject directly causes the death of the object."@en .
